<p><b>PeerGuardian</b> and <b>PeerGuardian 2</b> are <a href="/wiki/Free_software" title="Free software">free</a> and <a href="/wiki/Open_source" title="Open source">open source</a> programs developed by <a href="/wiki/Phoenix_Labs" title="Phoenix Labs">Phoenix Labs</a>. They are capable of blocking incoming and outgoing connections based on <a href="/wiki/IP_address" title="IP address">IP</a> <a href="/wiki/Blacklist_(computing)" title="Blacklist (computing)">blocklists</a>. The system is also capable of blocking custom ranges, depending upon user preferences.</p>
